        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Deflux is nice.  ToN has it's purpose too (high lag, raid areas, the resolve/refresh is much more anyway so you end up doing more damage).</P><P>The 53 and 56 pets have very low hp, but they're not meant to be tanks, /pet no taunt is your friend.  Set the 53 pet up for backstabs in a group, it's fun :).  The 56 monk is pretty impressive with the 61 damage melees even if it only has 1k of hp :).  It also won't kill ya to ask for people to buff your pet.  The 59 pet has skill level issues, although you do really have to consider how much it tears things apart with Mardu and AoD... Our undead only fears tend to be faster casts than our normal day-time ones an have a slightly better resist modifier I believe.  We also don't get any normal charms so undead charms are pretty useful (I know I've used Enslave Death a few times because people aren't paying attention).</P><P>Druids were actually the first class to get night-only spells as a sidenote.  As it does fit for us.  Levant is a highly useful ability (can ferry yourself across sg and a few other places).  No other class gets fixed duration invisibilities for undead and living.</P><P>Trucidation isn't meant to be a standard nuke at all (why I feel it really should be no resist graded considering it's cost).  It has potential to be very useful on high hp mobs.</P><P>Trepidation lasts one tick less than Invoke Fear at maximum duration, but has a 15 resist bonus, which is very significant, and means it will tend to actually last longer than invoke or at least land at all.</P><P>The Lich issue is odd definantively, I use Arch when I really don't need to be converting all that hp into mana, but it's still just a novelty.</P><P>The Blight be upon ye.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
