        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Wow.  Thanks for all the praise.  If anyone is going to the fan festival, feel free to print this out and confront them.  </P><P>I wasn't aware Druids had a night time only spell.  What would that be?</P><P>Our 53 & 56 pets have fewer hps than shaman pets.  We don't get upgrade pet only heals and the necro loses the ability to keep his pet alive.  Yes /pet no taunt is mandatory.  But we were a pet tanking class and we lose that ability.  We had a disposable tank that could buy a few seconds of time if things went bad.  Now 53 + 56 pets buy us 10 secs max IF the cleric buffed him.  The 59 has very few more hps than the 49.  It bothers me to see a shaman pet live longer than my pet, specialty or not.</P><P>My greavances with undead fear/charm is the fact that fear/charm work also.  What is the point of specialty spells?  They are undead and should require the specialty spells.  Here is an oppurtunity to give power to the undead hunters in some areas.  Undead aren't everywhere, but this would make our pets unfearable/uncharmable.</P><P>And you are mistaken.  Several classes get fixed duration invis, undead or not.  Druid, cleric, and wizards come to mind.</P><P>Trucidation is the only nuke anywhere with a 15 minute recast.  No one has this limitation.  I looked.  No one else has a nuke which requires 4 hours of someone else's gametime.  And this is our final reward at 60.  Feels like more of a slap in the face.</P><P>Sorry, but I just got sick of exploiting the game so I could use my spells.  In other words, once someone maxxed xp in level 60 would attack guards and die and die till 59.  Then I would sacrifice them 7 times and the rest of their corpses would be rezzed with the rez stick.  Ding 60 again with xp to earn again.</P><P>Nobody else has to do this.  It doesn't make sense and just feels like class dislike.</P><P>I would love if our duck stick summoned ghoul of death.  Or a summon corpse/rez spell with no component needed.  Or a pet buff from hell.  Anything which actually added value to our class.</P><P>As it stands.  I'm still watching from the sidelines waiting to see a point to play again.  Because it sure isn't going on raids to nuke big once every 15 minutes.  To be the worst pure nuking caster.  To be the class who's undead pet goes running in fear and get's munched.  To be standing on top of days and days played for the reward of the title</P><P>Exxon mana pump - full service.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
