        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">After playing a necro to 60, and giving it ALOT of thought on what I feel would help fix us, here are my ideas.</P><P><BR>Increase the 53,56,59 pets HP's by 25% and increasing their attacks by 5-10%</P><P>Make our pets immune to Fear, or add some different pet buff spells that have resistance components, but no haste added, then we could choose whether to buff our pets with haste/AC buff for damage output, or resistance buffs for longer life against casting mobs (like dragon AE's).</P><P>Lower the mana costs by 30% on our 50+ DoT's and our highest lifetaps/drains.</P><P>Make our 50+ lifetaps unresistable to any mob within our casting range, reduce the resistance rate and/or the taunt factor on some of our 50+ DoT's.</P><P><BR>These changes I feel would help make us a more viable damage dealer at higher levels, without overpowering us, and making almost no difference to the solo game.</P><P>Just my 2c</P><P>BTW, nice letter, well thought out and fairly well written, I just have one comment on it though.  It's a little long, I really hope someone at Verant actually takes the time to read it completely, and most important, you left out any ideas as to how these should be fixed, alot of what you have in there shows some obvious areas to help fix these problems, but remember, this is Verant, sometimes you have to lead the bull by the nose and give them the answers they haven't been able to come up with themselves :)</P><P><BR>Kiluudar Ravenwind  60 Warlock,  Fennin Ro,   T'kagi Ro</P><P>Edited by - Kiluudar on 05/22/2001  21:58:02<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

